
[1]equable

   E'QUABLE, a. [L. oequabilis, from oequus, equal, even, oeguo, to equal,
   to level.]

   1. Equal and uniform at all times, as motion. An equable motion
   continues the same in degree of velocity, neither accelerated nor
   retarded.

   2. Even; smooth; having a uniform surface or form; as an equable glove
   or plain.
